{"Posted:": "October  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "Saarland OR Telecommute, ideally from Germany", "Country:": "Germany", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "Do you have what it takes to rule?\rSkeletor, Magneto, and Dr. Evil. Three nefarious masterminds, and what do they have in common? They know that the first step to conquering the world is to have a really cool lair. We\u2019ve all spent a lot more time in our lairs lately, but is yours ready to be the site of domain dominance? If so, we have a killer remote role for you!\rOur client is an international IT company managing over 4 million domains for retail and corporate customers in 200 countries. Hold up\u2014200 countries? Talk about reach! To help achieve global domination, they\u2019re looking for a few top-notch senior Perl developers whose experience with implementing APIs and protocols is only matched by their drive to design and develop domain software solutions.\rLocated in St. Ingbert, Germany with a satellite office in Munich, this sociable and friendly team are now working 100% remotely. The situation with the pandemic-that-shall-not-be-named means this will continue for the foreseeable future, but when allowed back to the offices, you\u2019ll enjoy chillin\u2019 like a villain on their rooftop deck. Play a little air hockey, knock out a round of table soccer, and formulate your next plan to achieve global supremacy.\rThis successful global client is serving up a stellar working environment with great people, an interesting scope of tasks, and access to sharks with laser beams on their heads. The part about the sharks might be stretching it, but they do have a knack for attracting a strong team. Ready to be one of them? If you have experience with C/C++, like to work independently, and find creative solutions to technical problems, we want to hear from you. And if you\u2019re fluent in German as well as English? Major bonus points.\rThe quest for world domain domination starts now: are you in? If your lair is battle-ready, send us an email and let us know why you want to take over this role!", "Desired skills:": "Strong Modern Perl", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "November  7, 2020", "Company name:": "united-domains AG", "Location:": "Starnberg (Munich), Bavaria, Germany", "Country:": "Germany", "Pay rate:": "Euro", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "F\u00fcr unseren Standort in Starnberg bei M\u00fcnchen suchen wir zum n\u00e4chstm\u00f6glichen Termin Verst\u00e4rkung.\rAls Perl Software Developer bei der united-domains AG bist Du t\u00e4glich in die Entwicklung produktiver Systeme f\u00fcr unsere Kunden involviert. Dabei entwickelst Du je nach Erfahrung kleine Services alleine oder bearbeitest komplexere Themen gemeinsam mit erfahrenen Perl-Entwicklern. Unser Ziel ist es, innerhalb unserer Service orientierten Architektur, beste L\u00f6sungen f\u00fcr unsere Kunden anzubieten.\rWas wir bieten:\r- Freiraum in der Gestaltung Deiner Entwicklungst\u00e4tigkeit. Wir sind der \u00dcberzeugung, produktivere Arbeitsprozesse zu gewinnen, in dem wir keine strikten Vorgaben machen.\r- Konsequenter Verzicht auf Monolithen. Wir sind stets darauf bedacht, serviceorientiert zu planen und zu entwickeln. Dabei planen wir gemeinsam im Team und definieren Grenzen sowie Schnittstellen.\r- Innovation. Neues im Rahmen kleiner Projekte zu testen, steht bei uns vor \u201eDas haben wir schon immer so gemacht!\u201c.\r- Work-Life-Balance. Wir bieten Dir flexible Arbeitszeiten sowie die M\u00f6glichkeit des mobilen Arbeitens. Wir sind ein familienfreundliches Unternehmen und kennen die Anforderungen des Familienmanagements. Zudem ist der Weg zum Starnberger See nicht weit \u2013 welcher uns auch die Kulisse f\u00fcr unser abendliches Lauftraining bietet.", "Desired skills:": "Was Du bietest:\r- In Deiner Ausbildung hast Du die Prozesse der Softwareentwicklung bereits in der Theorie kennengelernt oder bist als \u201eSenior\u201c in der Lage diese gestalterisch anzuwenden.\r- Programmierkenntnisse in Perl oder einer \u00e4hnlichen Sprache (mit der Bereitschaft Perl zu lernen)\r- Damit sich die von Dir entwickelte Anwendung frei im Internet bewegen kann, wei\u00dft Du was DNS, TCP/IP und Linux-Networking bedeuten.\r- Mit SQL, Redis, GIT und Co. ist Dein Profil abgerundet und Du kannst Dich sofort produktiv integrieren.\r-Eventuell hast Du bereits erste Erfahrungen in asynchroner oder multithreaded Programmierung.\r- Flie\u00dfende Deutsch- und gute Englisch-Kenntnisse w\u00e4ren uns f\u00fcr die Verst\u00e4ndigung im Team wichtig.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Hast Du Interesse?\rDann sende uns Deine Bewerbung mit Foto, Lebenslauf und letztem Zeugnis an chancen@united-domains.de!\rAlle Unterlagen sollten in einem einzigen PDF-Dokument gespeichert sein. Die Dateigr\u00f6\u00dfe sollte 10 MB nicht \u00fcbersteigen."}
{"Posted:": "October 22, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "Canberra ACT, Australia", "Country:": "Australia", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "Extreme Recycling?\rScientists are a misunderstood crew. Consider pop culture: Dr. Frankenstein was just trying to improve the world. Sure, a guy made from corpse parts doesn\u2019t sound appealing, but what an innovative way to promote recycling. Talk about saving the planet one person at a time! If you think science is rad and want to work somewhere that agrees with you, our latest role might be perfect for you.\rOur client\u2019s area of expertise is decidedly less icky than ol\u2019 Frankenstein. Their unique software is used to provide genotyping information about crops, which in turn helps to develop new species of plants. Feeding the planet? Much better way to save the environment than repurposing a few arms and legs.\rWant to help them grow the next tomato-cucumber hybrid? They\u2019re looking for a bright mind with modern Perl skills. Sounds like you? Great. You don\u2019t happen have an interest in bioinformatics and genome technology, do you? You do? Well, if you tack on experience with Ansible, AWS, Linux containers, MySQL, Postgres, and Solr, then we know some completely non-monster-making science folks who want to talk to you.\rThis client\u2019s mission involves developing cost-efficient genotyping technology and promoting the development of crops adapted to suit their environment. They care about doing great things, and they want their team to be as happy as the crops they breed. To keep you smiling, they offer an excellent annual bonus, flexible working hours, and the ability to work much of your time from home (after the initial 6 months onsite in Canberra, of course. They have to show you the secret tomato-cucumber lab).\rDon\u2019t wait for lightning to strike\u2014your chance to make the world a better place is here! Send us an email today and let us know why you\u2019re the right choice for this fascinating role.", "Desired skills:": "Required:\r    Excellent Modern Perl skills, ideally with Dancer\r\n    At least some familiarity with JavaScript on the front-end\r\n    An openness to learning new things \u2013 there\u2019s a learning curve regarding the domain knowledge, but they\u2019ll be happy to teach you\r**Nice to have:\r**\r    MariaDB and Postgres\r\n    Exposure to biological and/or GIS data analysis\r\n    Ansible / AWS / Linux containers", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "November  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "London, UK OR Telecommute from Europe", "Country:": "United Kingdom", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "A Recipe for Success\rIn a world gone topsy-turvy, we have to appreciate the simple pleasures. Chocolate chip cookies fresh out of the oven, for instance. Or, for that matter, semi-stale cookies out of the bag. Turns out we\u2019re less picky about our biscuit choices, but one thing is for sure: a good recipe is the difference between a ho-hum snack and a melt-in-your-mouth chocolate extravaganza. We can\u2019t share the family cookie recipe (Mum would kill us) but we CAN share our latest client\u2019s recipe for success.\rAs an online tech publication with over 40 million readers around the world, they know a thing or two about keeping it fresh. Always on the cutting edge, their writers discourse on software, hardware, space, cloud services, culture, and electronics. Basically, they\u2019re experts on all the cool stuff you want to know about, so why not join them? They might even throw in a few complimentary snacks.\rWhile the client operates out of a London office, you also have the option to work remotely. Just think: in between managing their software projects from beginning to end, you could have your own tray of treats baking in the oven. A midday snack sounds like a great way to stay on task, which will be important because this small team only has room for self-starters who work solo as well as they work in a group.\rSo, besides baking up a storm, what will you be doing? Working as a Perl developer, you\u2019ll be responsible for consultation, design, development, testing, and deployment. While the snacks cool, you\u2019ll primarily use back-end Perl code on Debian servers with a smattering of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript thrown in for flavour.\rGot your mouth watering? If so, shoot us an email and let us know; there might just be a biscuit in it for you.", "Desired skills:": "Strong Perl is a must\r\n    DBIx::Class experience\r\n    Basic front-end skills / not scared of small amounts of JavaScript, HTML\r\n    Very comfortable on Linux, ideally Debian", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "November  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "Saarland OR Telecommute, ideally from Germany", "Country:": "Germany", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "Is that your Fancy Nightshirt?\rRemember when going to work meant changing out of your pyjamas, leaving home, and traveling to a secondary destination where you would spend approximately eight hours of your day? \u2026 yeah, neither do we. But we\u2019re told these things happened regularly less than a year ago, and one day, they may happen again. In the meantime, why not take a job with a company that may begin as a remote position and has the sort of staying power needed to make it through these unusual times, and have you skipping back to the office as soon as you can?\rIt\u2019s hard not to notice how much of our lives have moved online in recent months. Online shopping, socializing, working\u2014it\u2019s a digital world now, which is perfect for our client. As an international IT company managing millions of domains for retail and corporate customers in nearly every country in the world, they\u2019re busier than ever\u2014and they need a few senior Perl developers to help them continue to thrive. If you have strong experience implementing APIs and love designing and developing domain software solutions, you may be just the at-home hero they need.\rWhile their team is remote right now, this client operates out of St. Ingbert, Germany, with a satellite office in Munich. You\u2019re housebound for now, but when the world hops back onto its axis, you\u2019ll be eager to see their stellar offices. Let us paint a picture: a rooftop deck, table soccer and air hockey, a few pints with coworkers who sit less than six feet away \u2026 sounds idyllic, doesn\u2019t it?\rSo, how do you get your slipper-clad foot in the door? If you\u2019ve got experience with C/C++, enjoy working independently, and are a problem-solving whiz, you\u2019ve already done the hard part. And if you\u2019re fluent in German and English? Yes, please.\rWe won\u2019t be at home forever, and when we do go back to work, wouldn\u2019t you like to go somewhere with a rooftop deck? If the answer is \u201check yes,\u201d email us today!", "Desired skills:": "The ideal candidate should be confident using Modern Perl, in particular happy with DBIx::Class and Moose/Moo. Experience with any of mod_perl, Net::Server, Ubuntu, MySQL, Elastic Search, and memcached would be advantageous.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "October  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "Canberra ACT, Australia", "Country:": "Australia", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "Also, don\u2019t mess with dinosaurs.\rA handful of humans, an island teeming with dinosaurs, and a wicked storm bearing down\u2014what could go wrong? Our latest role won\u2019t send you out to be hunted by a gang of raptors, but if you found yourself intrigued by the science behind the movie, then we might have the perfect job for you.\rThis company\u2019s innovative software provides genotyping information about crops and is used to develop new species of plants. With your help, they\u2019ll continue to be on the cutting edge of science, but don\u2019t worry, they\u2019re not extracting dino DNA to bring back T-Rex\u2026 or are they? Guess you\u2019ll have to join the team to find out!\rTo make it to the inner circle, you need to have modern Perl skills. Ideally, you\u2019ll have an interest in genome technology and bioinformatics. If you spend your weekends reading science magazines and think smarter crops are key to our future, they want to hear from you. And if you happen to have experience with Ansible, AWS, Linux containers, MySQL, Postgres, and Solr, they\u2019ll be ready to fly you off to their private Costa Rican island for a meet-and-greet.\rWe might be stretching the truth about the private Costa Rican paradise, but with a mission that includes developing cost-efficient genotyping technology and promoting the development of crops adapted to suit their environment, this is a company that cares about doing great things. They want their people to be as happy as the crops they breed, so they offer an excellent annual bonus, flexible working hours, and the ability to work much of your time from home after the initial 6 months onsite in Canberra to get up to speed on the need-to-know details.\rIntrigued? If you want to know more about this role and you\u2019re located in Australia, send an email our way and let us know you want to be part of the next big thing in crop science!", "Desired skills:": "Required:\r    Excellent Modern Perl skills, ideally with Dancer\r\n    At least some familiarity with JavaScript on the front-end\r\n    An openness to learning new things \u2013 there\u2019s a learning curve regarding the domain knowledge, but they\u2019ll be happy to teach you\r**Nice to have:\r**\r    MariaDB and Postgres\r\n    Exposure to biological and/or GIS data analysis\r\n    Ansible / AWS / Linux containers", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "October 28, 2020", "Company name:": "Deriv.com", "Location:": "Cyberjaya, Selangor, Malaysia", "Country:": "Malaysia", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "Our team\r\nWe are the Back-end team, the team responsible for designing, developing, testing, and debugging the company's server-side apps and databases. In collaboration with the QA team, we investigate and resolve technical issues. We empower the Front-end team by providing the components and features that they need. We aspire to delight our customers with a flawless digital experience.\rAbout us\r\nFounded in 1999, Deriv.com (formerly Binary.com) is a pioneer in online trading. We enable our customers to trade on the world\u2019s financial markets. Focused on customer-centric solutions, we aspire to be the world\u2019s leading online trading service provider.\rA career at Deriv.com offers you the opportunity to make an impact in a fast-growing organisation that\u2019s at the cutting edge of online trading technology.\rYour role\r\nAs a Senior Perl Developer at Deriv.com, you will write robust, high-quality, and production-ready code that empowers our websites and applications. Your work will directly influence the core architecture that drives our high-traffic binary options trading website.\r\nWhat you\u2019ll do\r\n-Develop and maintain world-class web applications.\r\n-Build, maintain, and optimise the technology that powers our servers, applications, and databases.\r\n-Work closely with other teams to come up with effective architecture to support the deployment of new products and features.\r\n-Troubleshoot and debug problems in existing applications, and find new ways to improve their speed, functionality, and scalability.\r\n-Participate in all aspects of the product lifecycle.", "Desired skills:": "What you have\r\n-Deep Perl expertise\r\n-Expertise in Linux system administration\r\n-Experience with relational database design, and/or open-source RDBMS systems such as MySQL and PostgreSQL\r\n-Familiarity with Perl DBI, Moose, PSGI/Plack, nginx, JavaScript, Redis, and Git\r\n-Ability to produce high-quality, self-documenting code by using test-driven development (TDD) techniques\r\n-Event-driven programming in Perl\r\n-Passion for Linux, and other open-source platforms\r\n-Excellent spoken and written English communication skills\rWhat we\u2019ll give you\r\n-Growth-inducing challenges\r\n-Productive work atmosphere\r\n-Cooperation, support, and empowerment\r\n-Career progression opportunities\r\n-Market-based salary\r\n-Annual performance bonus\r\n-Health benefits\r\n-Casual dress code\r\n-Travel and internet allowances\rLocation\r\nCyberjaya, Malaysia\rAbout location\r\nCyberjaya is a well-planned township with no shortage of residences, restaurants, retail outlets and recreational facilities. Blending urban development with nature, Cyberjaya is rich with lush greenery, lakes and parks, making it ideal for work and play. The Maju Expressway (MEX) conveniently connects Cyberjaya to Kuala Lumpur city and the rest of the Klang Valley, while the Dedicated Transport Services (DTS) provides reliable transportation for those commuting to and from Cyberjaya. Thirty minutes away from KL city centre, our Cyberjaya office is where you can experience the ultimate work-life balance.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "recruitment@deriv.hr"}
{"Posted:": "November  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "Vienna, Austria", "Country:": "Austria", "Pay rate:": "Competitive salary based on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "Where can you find hundreds of cafes, wiener schnitzel, and entertainment ranging from the uber-posh Opera Ball to the fabulously flamboyant LGBT Life Ball? Why, in the same city that is the birthplace of Mozart and consistently ranks as the best place in the world to live: say hello to vivacious Vienna!\rIf your hometown isn\u2019t nestled between gorgeous vineyards and jaw-dropping palaces, maybe it\u2019s time to see what our client has to offer. As one of the largest product and price comparison platforms in German-speaking countries, they know all about finding the best products at a price that would make Mozart shout, \u201cWunderbar!\u201d They want to find a Perl programmer who thrives on delivering quality content, well-executed user information that\u2019s easy to understand, and is as committed to transparency and excellence as they are.\rAll work and no play would have made even Mozart a dull boy; fortunately, there are tons of fun things to do when you clock out. Their cultural scene is legendary, with many concerts, exhibitions, and productions throughout the year. Whether you\u2019re after a day of museums or a tour through one of Vienna\u2019s ultra-lavish palaces, there\u2019s plenty to see and do.\rNo doubt a weekend of strolling through history will leave you with a mighty appetite during the work week. Not to worry\u2014your new employer has thought of that. Team members are provided with delicious and nutritious lunch options every day, all completely on the house. Think of it: the extra time you would have spent packing a sack lunch is now prime sleep-in time.\rSo, if you\u2019re interested, send us an email and say _auf Wiedersehen _to your current job!", "Desired skills:": "Client is willing to consider all candidates with strong Perl, but they make heavy use of PostgreSQL, Elasticsearch, and Dancer, any of which would be useful to have experience with.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "November 25, 2020", "Company name:": "MediaAlpha", "Location:": "Redmond, WA", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "Competitive", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "yes", "Description:": "We are looking for a talented Senior Perl Software Engineer to join our technology team. As a Senior Perl Software Engineer at MediaAlpha, you will take part in all aspects of the software development lifecycle. You'll love it! Our entire platform is in Perl leveraging a light Mason framework. You will get to work directly with stakeholders in defining our MediaAlpha Exchange Product and developing and testing new features and integrations. The ideal candidate will enjoy designing, implementing, and scaling systems that process tens of thousands of high-value transactions a day, while also producing elegant and readable code.\rResponsibilities\rOwn the full software development lifecycle of implementing high-performance ad serving software.\r\nIntegrate our products with our partners.\r\nPerl code development in a Linux environment, on Amazon EC2, leveraging also S3, CloudFront and Route 53.\r\nWork as a member of the team, jumping in to help out and resolve routine issues.\r\nLead in representing the engineering team in product planning and architecting.\r\nBe part of a team that maintains and supports our live MediaAlpha Exchange product.", "Desired skills:": "Requirements\r5+ years experience in software development.\r\nSubstantial Perl development experience in Unix/Linux operating environments a MUST.\r\nStrong SQL skills and understanding of database and query optimizations. \r\nWorking knowledge of MySQL a plus.\r\nExperience using web APIs.\r\nAbility to write elegant and readable code.\r\nAbility to maintain live production systems.\r\nA self-starter, comfortable with ambiguity and ability to problem solve while paying careful attention to detail.\r\nStrong programming skills including software engineering methodologies and best practices.\r\nExperience working with engineers and non-technical stakeholders.\r\nBe a champion of instilling excellence in coding and quality into the team and culture.\r\nAbility to articulate and communicate clearly, concisely, and thoughtfully.\r\nOrganized and self-motivated.\r\nAmazon EC2 experience a plus.\r\nB.S. required, preferably in a technical discipline (e.g., computer science).", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": ""}
{"Posted:": "November  7, 2020", "Company name:": "RG Nets, Inc.", "Location:": "United States", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "up to 225000", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "We are looking for network engineers who have who have become software developers. Alternatively we would like to find software developers who have significant experience with network engineering. The ideal candidate will have current or have previously held certifications (CCNA/NP/IE, CWNA/NP/NE, etc.) and has decided to change career paths into software development. Environments that we use in our product include, but are not limited to, Ruby on Rails, Perl, Expect, JavaScript and UNIX shell all running on FreeBSD.\rThe revenue eXtraction gateway (rXg) is our one and only product. It is deployed by the largest telcos in the world. The backend of the rXg is huge Perl daemon that is approximately 15 years old. It speaks to the same database instance as a RoR web GUI through code generated from Ruby migrations. We're looking for one or more Perl wizards to improve our system. \rDetails about RG Nets that you should know before you apply:\rRG Nets is a very small company and it is run by crazy people... arguably it's really the leader who is truly insane, but in any case... it shows... in everything we do.\rWe have a short meeting in the morning every weekday ... which we start by doing 30 push-ups while holding planks between them for 3 minutes and 30 seconds to the Moby track Flower (some call this the \"bring sally up challenge\") ... and yes, you did read that right, we do that every before every meeting.\rOur corporate meetings are usually held at race tracks and often involve riding motorcycles at 150 MPH. Our corporate training events usually involve copious amounts of alcohol and firearms ... in that order. This is not a joke, nor is it intended \"to try make us sound like badasses.\" We actually enjoy what we do and we believe that it helps promote the creative process and the business as a whole. Photographic evidence can be found on social media.\rThe rXg runs premier sites worldwide... including the busiest airports in the world, stadiums where teams you've heard of (and are on prime time OTA TV) play, piles of hotels and time shares in beautiful and exotic locations ... and as an employee you can volunteer to help with these installs. The selfies you will take while doing this are priceless.\rRG Nets is a high intensity environment and a meritocracy. We pay market rates to start. If you deserve a raise because you exceed our very high expectations, you will get it, on the spot. People who have worked with us for a while make far higher than market rates.\rThere are some people who enjoy disparaging us. Some of these folks are quite vocal and spew their crap all over the Internet as well as in person. We don't care. We've been busy making a magnificent product and running a profitable company (no external investors) for the past 15 consecutive years. We are busy changing the world, every single day. We are looking for people who are thick skinned and like minded.\rRG Nets has been a fully remote work environment for all employees since its inception. Other people are trying to figure out remote work. We've had it figured out for over a decade. People work when they can. People take off when they want to. We all get what we need to get done, that's all that matters.\rYou probably ought to read-up about RG Nets before you apply, because if you do apply, you may get a call within a few minutes, yes even on a weekend or late at night... because we are always working. If we call you then you should be ready to have in depth discussions about what we do immediately.\rTell us why you want to work with us. Most importantly, show us your code.", "Desired skills:": "Demonstrable experience as a Software Engineer or Software Developer (show us your code)\rExperience designing interactive applications\rAbility to develop software in Perl and if possible Ruby as well\rExcellent knowledge of relational databases (PostGreSQL)\rProficiency in software engineering tools such as git\rAbility to document requirements and specifications as well as write user manual entries", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "info@rgnets.com"}
{"Posted:": "December  3, 2020", "Company name:": "Undisclosed Stealth Project", "Location:": "New York, NY, USA", "Pay rate:": "Commensurate with experience USD", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Independent contractor (hourly)", "Hours:": "Part time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "I have a project where I'm looking for a few part time perl people (as well as a front-end person and a marketing/PR person). I'm in NYC, but remote work is fine as long as you can work independently well and we can meet virtually 1-2 times a week to discuss progress.", "Desired skills:": "The site is being developed using Perl/MySQL/Bootstrap/github along with some Machine Learning and Mojo websocket client components. (We are not wed to any particular technology, except perl). We are seeking people who are strong in at least two (but not necessarily all) of these skills:\r\n* perl development\r\n* database development\r\n* unix system administration\r\n* machine learning/ai\r\n* design and web front end (CSS/JS/Bootstrap/JQuery/Vue/Plotly/etc)\u2028\r\n* written and spoken communication (this is very important)\u2028\rSeparately, I'm also seeking someone with strong marketing/PR skills to help target and attract customers. \rPlease email with your resume and hourly rate and we'll talk! Also feel free to forward this to people that you think would be appropriate and interested.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "joshr-jobsperlorg@joshr.com"}
{"Posted:": "August 18, 2020", "Company name:": "mroads LLC", "Location:": "REMOTE, Dallas, TX", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "$40-$45", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Hourly employee", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "Software Development Engineer Test (SDET II)\rProfessional experience in Software Application Development with distributed architecture and designed using Perl, Web Technologies and other related technologies. Proven track record writing complex SQL Queries, Cursors, Stored Procedures, functions, packages, tables, views, triggers and data connectivity and data integration of backend databases.Passionate about testing and especially automated testing and can talk about the successes they have achieved through automation. \r\nThis individual will be a pivotal member of an Agile Scrum team working closely with product owners, front end developers and backend developers to drive a successful testing strategy. This individual should be passionate about testing and delivering quality via test automation. \rResponsibilities:\r\n\u2022\tHands on engineer with ability to code in various programming languages \r\n\u2022\tAssist in design and development of Perl applications.\r\n\u2022\tPerform application modifications and enhancements based on business needs.\r\n\u2022\tDevelop clean, high-quality and reusable codes based on programming standards.\r\n\u2022\tCoordinate with build teams to clearly understand business requirements and expectations.\r\n\u2022\tConduct trainings and provide guidance to other team members when required.\r\n\u2022\tSuggest optimal application development solutions to meet or exceed business objectives.\r\n\u2022\tDevelop best practices to ensure coding efficiency and quality.\r\n\u2022\tAnalyze and resolve coding issues in a timely and accurate manner.\r\n\u2022\tPrepare and maintain coding documentations for reference purposes.\r\n\u2022\tDemonstrated experience in test automation development, using frameworks and tools like Junit, TestNG, Appium, Cucumber, Postman as well as REST/JSON APIs.\r\n\u2022\tVerifiable experience in building and deploying CI systems such Jenkins, Bamboo. Hands-on experience building CI automation pipelines using Jenkins, Docker.\r\n\u2022\tData driven, with strong problem-solving skills with analytical capabilities to be able to support theories/solutions using underlying data.\r\n\u2022\tKnowledge of Cloud based Web Applications Architecture.\r\n\u2022\tKnowledge of deployment technologies with emphasis on AWS Cloud. \r\n\u2022\tGood Understanding of the CI and CD.\r\n\u2022\tMust have worked on the SQL queries and other Database scripts.\r\n\u2022\tHands On knowledge of using the No-SQL databases like Couchbase etc.\r\n\u2022\tThorough understanding of concurrency, threading, algorithms, and data structures\r\n\u2022\tGood Front End UI experience on HTML, CSS and Javascript.\r\n\u2022\tCreate and execute SQL queries and validate databases using an automation tool.", "Desired skills:": "Qualification:\r\n\u2022\tBachelor\u2019s / Master\u2019s degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, related Engineering field and a minimum of 3-5 years of experience with test automation tools and development in a product engineering organization\r\n\u2022\t3+ years of technical experience with emphasis in PERL, mod Perl, Object-oriented PERL, PERL regex UNIX shell scripting.\r\n\u2022\tExperience working with SSH client on the Linux Operating System.\r\n\u2022\tExperience in developing middleware components for software in C/C++ using STL, multi-threading, data structures, IPC (TCP/IP socket programming), SNMP, and design patterns.\r\n\u2022\tExperience in object-oriented programming using C/C++ on various flavors of Linux (Ubuntu, SUSE), QNX, VxWorks, and WinCE.\r\n\u2022\tContribute and build tools, Ksh, Csh, Perl scripts for the application and writing the Make files to compile the programs as per DXC technology internal project standards.\r\n\u2022\t3+ years of experience in CSS and Javascript scripting. 3+ years of experience in developing against Apache Web server, Hand-on experience in core Java and J2EE, XML, XSLT, XPATH\r\n\u2022\t3+ years transact SQL/stored procedure development experience.\r\n\u2022\tStrong in Unix/Linux, Linux/BSD command-line skills, understanding of Unix/Linux environment/Kernel calls\r\n\u2022\t2-5 years of experience in Microservices, Web services experience using SOAP and REST-based service & XML, JSON. Experience with CI/CD tools such as Jenkins and GIT and other relevant tools\r\n\u2022\t2-3 years of experience in creating frameworks that utilize and interact with DevOps tools such as Couchbase, JIRA, Stash, Bamboo, Confluence, Ready API - Soap UI Pro, Ready API \u2013 ServiceV, Git, Jenkins", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "rakesh@mroads.com"}
{"Posted:": "August 18, 2020", "Company name:": "Greeting Card Universe", "Location:": "Danville, CA United States", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "$70k to $100k", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Independent contractor (hourly)", "Hours:": "Flexible", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "Looking for an experienced Linux, Perl, MySQL programmer. We are an exciting and team oriented small company located in Danville, looking for a responsible and meticulous individual who enjoys small companies and is excited to be a member of the core group of an exciting, growing company. The candidate would work remotely for our technical lead to design and develop additional features and integrate our online website and mobile environments. You will tackle specific projects from start to finish relating to significant feature improvements for our main website.\rThis is a remote position, but we are expecting a fulltime commitment. If you plan on juggling this job with other commitments, this will not be a good fit for us.\rThe company\u2019s focus is 100% ecommerce in the B2C environment. Over the past 12 years we have become the world\u2019s largest greeting card store with over 600,000 unique paper cards created by a crowd sourced environment of over 4,000 worldwide artists. There is significantly more potential ahead.\rResponsibilities:\r\nWeb development using Perl and MySQL on LAMP environment (Linux, Apache, MySQL, Perl)\r\nUsing Github for Git repository administration\r\nDevelop new features, enhancements and bug fixes\r\nProvide technical support of production systems\r\nAddress issues related to system stability, scalability, performance and security\r\nHelp maintain 24x7 availability of production systems\rThis position is flexible.   We can do Salary or Independent contractor.  Parttime or fulltime.", "Desired skills:": "Minimum 4 years of programming experience\r\nBS in computer science or related field\r\nExperience with Linux, servers, network and firewall administration, intrusion detection, etc.\r\nWeb development with HTML, CSS, Javascript\r\nExperience developing with Perl\r\nExperience developing with PHP\r\nExperience with Prototype (or similar AJAX library)\r\nExperience working with Apache\r\nMySQL Database development experience\r\nExperience with Git Version Control System\r\nGood written and oral communication skills\r\nSelf motivated problem solver that works well within a team\rExperience with mod_perl\r\nExperience with Networks, Firewalls, Switches, Loadbalancers\r\nAgile software development experience\r\nKnowledge of internet protocols and standards (TCP/IP, HTTP, SSL, SMTP, XML, SOAP, etc.)\r\nExperience with shell scripting\r\nExperience with high-volume or critical production service environment\r\nExperience with ImageMagick", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "jobs@bigdates.com\rGreetingCardUniverse.com\r\n154 East Prospect Avenue, Suite B\r\nDanville, CA 94526\r\n925-866-4111"}
