{"Posted:": "December  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Ambra Health", "Location:": "New York, NY (Remote)", "Country:": "United States", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "AmbraHealth is modernizing medical care with our cloud-based image management suite. Demand for new medical solutions has increased during COVID. Come join our growing team and do meaningful work that has a direct and immediate contribution to patient care.\rWe\u2019re looking to hire a few Senior Perl Engineers to work on the Ambra services API, a large-scale, Perl/Postgres/Redis application that sits at the center of the Ambra suite of products. This application provides REST endpoints that are responsible for providing control and access to all of the data (study, patient, image, etc) and it contains all of the business logic (authentication, permissions, associations, rules, etc) for workflows managing billions of medical images.\rWe are a permanently remote engineering team. We were pre-COVID and will continue to be be post-COVID.\rOur hiring process includes an option to do a short, well paid, part time consulting project to determine if we\u2019re the right place for you.", "Desired skills:": "- Productive self-starter, proactive, organized, own your code\r\n- Industry experience with full stack architecture and distributed systems\r\n- Ability to focus on customer requirements, look past own interests \r\n- Solid knowledge of Perl, PostgreSQL, Linux, REST API, and SAAS technologies\r\n- Firm grasp of SQL, indexes, joins, query performance\r\n- Familiar with in-memory caches (like Redis and Memcached)\r\n- Industry experience with high performance/throughput data processing\r\n- Strong problem-solving abilities", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Send resume and cover letter to mike+jobs@ambrahealth.com."}
{"Posted:": "November  7, 2020", "Company name:": "GreenRope", "Location:": "San Diego, CA", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "USD - commensurate with experience", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Independent contractor (hourly)", "Hours:": "Flexible", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "GreenRope has a position for a perl programmer with Appcelerator/Titanium experience to help support, extend, and bugfix our mobile app.\rYou'll work in Appcelerator alloy and webview code to build the UI, and in the perl backend/api. You'll also need to have experience with itunesconnect and developer.android.com to manage test and production releases. We're also trying to automate releasing with fastlane - there will be a nice chunk of time spent in there.\rIts possible (likely, even) that the app will be migrated to Vue or similar with an OpenAPI backend and we'd lean heavily on your expertise there.\rTheres also lots of general web ux/javascript work available as well.", "Desired skills:": "Required:\r\nAppcelerator/Titanium\r\nPerl\r\nFastlane\r\nJavaScript\rDesired:\r\nMySQL\r\nOpenAPI\r\nDevOps\r\nCentOS\r\nWeb Frontend UX/JS\r\nCKEditor", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "jobs@greenrope.com"}
{"Posted:": "December  9, 2020", "Company name:": "MSTS", "Location:": "Overland Park, KS or Remote", "Country:": "United States", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "MSTS is a growing global FinTech company specializing in billing and payment solutions with a strong commitment to our customers. By harnessing 40 years of experience, technology investments and a desire to help businesses reach their full potential, we have expanded our portfolio of credit and payments technology solutions and blended them with a unique local touch that drives deeply into geo-specific business processes and payments. Create value for our business partners by delivering innovative solutions and logistics through a global team of local professionals.\rWe are looking for results oriented, enthusiastic individuals who thrive in a fast paced environment and love technology. In this role you will be at the forefront of our innovation working on complex payment solutions that include extensive internationalization and integration with partner systems. If you are an entrepreneur at heart and love writing code you\u2019ve found your next home.\rEssential Responsibilities:\rIntegrate data from various back-end services and databases\r\nLead solution design and development of web applications\r\nWork with product management, end users and other stakeholders to define product solutions\r\nBuild and consume REST/SOAP APIs from various back-end services and databases\r\nWrite clean, high-quality, high-performance, maintainable code\r\nWork collaboratively as part of an cross functional team that includes designers, customers, testers, internal stakeholders and other software engineers\r\nProvide software engineering coaching and mentorship to other engineers\r\nResearch and stay current in architecture and development practices and trends\rRequirements:\r10+ years of software development experience\r\n\u201cFull stack\u201d architect / lead software engineer with experience in multiple languages\r\nTrack record of playing a significant role in the creation of business critical web applications running in production\r\nExperience implementing CI/CD automation tools and practices\r\nExperience with RDBMS/SQL or PostgreSQL\r\nHighly proficient technical skills with one or more of the following programming languages: JavaScript, TypeScript, Ruby, Perl, PL/SQL, or SQL\r\nHighly proficient technical skills using one or more of the following front-end MV* frameworks such as Vue.js, Quasar, Angular, Ionic, React, or Rails (Ruby)\r\nExperience using any cloud based platforms like AWS, Docker, or Kubernetes\r\nExperience with one or more of the following : Nginx, Apache, Oracle, Postgresql, MongoDB, Phusion Passenger, or uwsgi servers\r\nIntermediate understanding of Jenkins, Browserstack (usage), Git, SSH, Docker, Helm, or AWS Console\r\nIntermediate level understanding of the UNIX operating system\r\nIntermediate understanding of standard microservices, MVC, and Service Orientated architectures.\r\nUnderstanding of Agile software delivery principles and practices \r\nThe ability to follow industry best practices and produce good level of quality\r\nA degree in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent combination of education and experience\rOutstanding Applicants Should:\rFocus on continuous learning and improvement\r\nDemonstrated initiative\r\nProven positive impact on end user experience\r\nAgile Advocate and driven to improve team effectiveness\r\nSelf-motivated and confident with an ownership mentality\r\nAutonomous producer\rWhy you will love working at MSTS:\rCompetitive salary\r\nGenerous paid time off\r\nMedical, dental, vision, FSA, Life/AD&D, long and short term disability\r\n401K matching\r\nCasual environment and dress\r\nEmployee referral program\rAt MSTS we believe:\rIn saying yes to unique and challenging requirements\r\nEmpowered team members are creative team members\r\nOur products make the customer\u2019s day just a little bit better\r\nWork/life balance makes us all more effective  \r\nMSTS is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer.  We welcome all veterans and disabled applicants.", "Desired skills:": "Required: \r\nExtensive Perl\rStand Out:\r\nOracle Database\r\nJavaScript\r\nXML\r\nRuby\r\nAWS", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Apply on the website"}
{"Posted:": "September 12, 2020", "Company name:": "Key-Systems Gmbh", "Location:": "St. Ingbert, Germany", "Country:": "Germany", "Pay rate:": "Euro", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "Zur Verst\u00e4rkung unseres innovativen Teams suchen wir zum n\u00e4chstm\u00f6glichen Zeitpunkt einen Softwareentwickler (m/w/d) f\u00fcr unseren Gesch\u00e4ftsbereich RRPproxy.\r\nUnser Firmensitz befindet sich in St. Ingbert im Saarland/Deutschland. Bei Bedarf kann die Stelle aber auch remote aus Europa ausge\u00fcbt werden. In diesem Fall w\u00fcrde lediglich die Einarbeitung in St. Ingbert stattfinden.\rWir suchen dich f\u00fcr folgende Aufgaben:\r +   Neu- und Weiterentwicklung komplexer Softwarel\u00f6sungen im Domain-Gesch\u00e4ft\r\n +   Optimierung und Weiterentwicklung des Backend-Systems\r\n +   Mitarbeit bei der Erweiterung des TLD-Angebots, sowie bei technischen Registry Relations\r\n  +  Analyse und L\u00f6sung der von Kunden und Partnern gemeldeten technischen Probleme\r\n +   Test und Dokumentation alter und neuer Funktionalit\u00e4ten", "Desired skills:": "Wir suchen genau dich, wenn du:\r +   ein Informatikstudium oder abgeschlossene IT-Ausbildung mit Programmiererfahrung oder eine vergleichbare Ausbildung hast,\r\n  +  bereits Erfahrung im Dokumentieren von neuen oder bestehenden Prozessen sowie Kenntnisse in der Durchf\u00fchrung von qualit\u00e4tssichernden Ma\u00dfnahmen sammeln konntest,\r\n  +  in der Implementierung bestehender APIs und Protokolle (z.B. EPP, SOAP) erfahren bist,\r\n  +  in der Sprache Perl oder vergleichbaren Sprachen programmieren kannst (Kenntnisse in C / C++ sind hilfreich)\r\n  +  \u00fcber sehr gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift verf\u00fcgst (weitere Fremdsprache von Vorteil),\r\n  +  gute Analyse- und L\u00f6sungskompetenz bei technischen Problemen besitzt, hohe Leistungsbereitschaft und Flexibilit\u00e4t, sowie eine selbst\u00e4ndige Arbeitsweise mitbringst.\r\n  W\u00fcnschenswert w\u00e4ren zus\u00e4tzlich Kenntnisse von SQL (MySQL), im Domain-Gesch\u00e4ft und Kenntnisse der Funktionsweise von Nameservern (DNS).", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Wenn Du dich gerne in einem unb\u00fcrokratischen, motivierten Team weiterentwickeln m\u00f6chtest und eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten in einem internationalen Umfeld sowie Herausforderungen sch\u00e4tzt,\r\ndann bewirb dich jetzt mit Gehaltsvorstellung und fr\u00fchestem Eintrittstermin am besten per E-Mail (als PDF-Datei) an:\r\njobs@key-systems.net\r\nz.Hd. Frau Pfeiffer"}
{"Posted:": "October  1, 2020", "Company name:": "cPanel", "Location:": "Houston, TX", "Country:": "United States", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "cPanel provides one of the industry's most reliable and intuitive hosting automation software platforms. This position will assist in the maintenance, development and implementation of existing software systems and/or applications for market sale. Participates in the full development life cycle and consults with senior peers on non-complex projects.\rEssential Functions:  \rCreates code specification proposals and prototypes for review by team and stakeholders\r\nDevelops well designed, testable, and efficient new code and modifies existing code based on stakeholder requirements for cPanel products and systems\r\nDocuments code in detail for future reference\r\nParticipates in the use of established development standards and continuously contributes positively to improve the quality of development standards based on data driven decisions\r\nImplements test plans and tests based on current cPanel standards and aides in improving the testing standards\r\nAnalyzes code to find causes of errors and refactors existing code to optimize performance\r\nCollaborates with teams to resolve issues and deliver products of high quality\r\nParticipates in project demos, presentations and meetings\r\nAdheres to the policies and procedures of the company\r\nExemplifies the Core Values of Integrity, Respect, Collaboration and Follow-through\rAdditional Duties:\rReceives instruction and feedback from other developers\r\nSeeks out and collects local, as well as third party sourced data, to make business appropriate, data driven decisions\r\nAdvises and mentors other developers in design and implementation processes pertinent to cPanel\r\nOperates in both Kanban and Agile/Scrum teams interchangeably without a negative impact to productivity\r\nConsistently maintains a full workload without direct oversight\r\nOther tasks and duties as deemed necessary", "Desired skills:": "Technical skills:\rProgramming language expertise in Perl/PHP/Python; Git; bug tracking, troubleshooting; Linux command line usage\r\nExpertise in two or more of the following: Unit testing; database access; Web Servers (apache, LiteSpeed, nginx); SQL Servers (MariaDB, MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc), Mail Servers (Exim, Sendmail, etc) DNS Servers (BIND), and Linux Filesystems (ext3/4, xfs)\r\nAble to perform effective code reviews\r\nExperience with multiple programming languages\r\nAbility to operate in both Kanban and Agile/Scrum teams interchangeably without a negative impact to productivity\rEducation/Experience:\rBachelors degree in relevant field or equivalent experience\r\nFive years of Linux / BSD / *nix system troubleshooting or a related certification (RHCE)\r\nFive years of Perl, PHP, or Python development experience\r\nTravel -  Occasional local and/or overnight travel may be required, some by interstate air", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "John Syed\r\nj.syed@cpanel.net\r\n832-946-1613"}
{"Posted:": "September 29, 2020", "Company name:": "MaxMind, Inc.", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "MaxMind  (www.maxmind.com) is looking for a talented and highly motivated person to help us improve our minFraud risk score. minFraud is used to screen over 2 billion online transactions a year, the majority of those being e-commerce.\rWe are hiring anywhere in Canada and in the following US states: AK, CA, CO, FL, IN, LA, MA, MI, MN, MT, NY (excluding New York City and Yonkers), NC, NH, NV, OR, PA, SD, TX, VA, UT, WA, WV, WY.\rThe Position Overview\rOur risk scoring is based on heuristics and machine learning. Your role would be to improve the heuristics as well as feature engineering for machine learning.\rPotential improvements are back-tested against fraud and not-fraud reports from customers. Our fraud analyst team helps analyze the results and suggests improvements. This work is meaningful since even a small improvement can help customers reduce fraud significantly given our scale.\rOur Development Practices\rCurrently most of our risk score code is written in Perl and runs on Linux. We plan to move this code to Go over the next few years. We maintain fast development cycles and identify small, incremental improvements that add up over time. All work goes through internal code review on GitHub Enterprise.\rWe use open source software as much as possible, and we release code back to the community when we can do so.\rWhy work at MaxMind?\r\nIn a recent survey, employees listed feeling respected, trusted, and valued and having autonomy as things they most liked. They also liked having good colleagues.\rMaxMind has a social mission. We are passionate about helping our customers avoid fraud, and 70% of profits after taxes are donated to charity.\rMaxMind\u2019s compensation strives to reward getting stuff done, quality of work, and working well with others.\rMore about working at MaxMind\r\nMaxMind is a casual, friendly, results-focused company of about 40 employees, about half of whom are in technical positions. We maintain a set of core, overlapping hours, but we\u2019re flexible with specific start and end times and are understanding about appointments and life events.\rCompensation includes a competitive salary and participation in a company performance-based bonus plan. All employees get a $2k professional development budget and five days for professional development annually.\rIn addition to medical, dental, and vision coverage, we offer several other benefits in the US, including a 401k with employer contribution and FSA. Please inquire about benefits in Canada.\rOur development team is largely comprised of telecommuters, so communication centers around group chat, agile planning tools, and Google Meet. Full-time telecommuting is permitted.\rDiversity and Inclusion\r\nWe're committed to diversity and inclusion and are mindful of incorporating them into all aspects of our company. New ideas and perspectives come from diverse ways of seeing and thinking. MaxMind is sensitive to all individuals and viewpoints and believes everyone\u2019s contributions and opinions are valuable assets to our team. We value bringing individuals and different perspectives together within and across every department.\rWe encourage and sincerely welcome applications from candidates of color, women, queer candidates, candidates with family caregiving responsibilities, transgender candidates, and from other communities not well represented in the tech world.\rIf you have suggestions on how we may better promote or express our commitment to diversity and inclusion, we would love to hear from you. Please send your suggestions to hr@maxmind.com.", "Desired skills:": "Minimum Qualifications:\r- Experience creating and testing heuristics for fraud detection using\r\n  online data like IP addresses and emails.\r\n- Programming experience, at least intermediate level (a programming\r\n  exercise will be given to all applicants)\r\n- Interested in learning Perl and Go\rDesired\r\n- SQL experience\r\n- Experience with git, Linux/Unix and command line tools", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Resumes without cover letters will not be considered. We want to know about you, please share any projects or accomplishments and include a link so we can learn more. One of the first steps in our interviewing process is a homework assignment, and we will ask you for a submission so we can gain insight into your work.\rMaxMind does not currently sponsor US employment visas. For Canadian candidates, you must be eligible/authorized to work in Canada. \rPlease apply here -"}
{"Posted:": "October  1, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "London, UK OR Telecommute from Europe", "Country:": "United Kingdom", "Pay rate:": "Depending on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "Back to \u2026 work?\rThere\u2019s nothing like autumn to remind you of back-to-school. Newly sharpened pencils, new sneakers, the slickest Trapper Keeper on the block. Wait, do kids even write manually anymore, or is it all emojis? Doesn\u2019t matter. Whether you\u2019re an eleven-year-old with scraped-up knees or a thirty-eight-year-old whose knees ache after a run, one thing remains the same: you want to learn about cool stuff, and where better to work than a place with the scoop on all the fascinating things you wish they taught in school?\rOur client is a leading online tech publication with more than 40 millions readers worldwide. Their articles cover electronics, hardware, software, AI, space, cloud services, and culture. They know what\u2019s hot in the world of computers, and they tell the world all about it in crisp, engaging articles that are read from London, England, to London, Ontario. Don\u2019t know where London, Ontario is? Maybe it\u2019s time for a geography class refresher.\rThis tech talk titan operates out of a London office that offers the opportunity to work remotely. Keep your eyes on your own paper\u2014this is a small, self-motivated team that thrives on working independently as well as collaborating. Unlike those school group assignments where you could fob the hard work off on someone else, everyone on this team has to pull their weight.\rIf this sounds like the role for you, toss us a note in class. Better yet, send us an email\u2014less chance the teacher will see.", "Desired skills:": "Strong Perl is a must\r\n    DBIx::Class experience\r\n    Basic front-end skills / not scared of small amounts of JavaScript, HTML\r\n    Very comfortable on Linux, ideally Debian", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "October  2, 2020", "Company name:": "Perl Jobs by Perl Careers", "Location:": "South Cambridge, United Kingdom", "Country:": "United Kingdom", "Pay rate:": "Competitive salary based on experience", "Poster represents:": "a recruiting agency", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "Perl jobs can be pretty similar, and we write a lot of job ads at Perl Careers. The overwhelming majority of Perl jobs, you\u2019re writing a web-app. For some companies, that\u2019s a web-app that integrates with giant robots, and for some companies that\u2019s a web-app that shoots money all across the world, but fundamentally you\u2019ll be cracking out Mojolicious or Catalyst or Dancer, and writing some model and controller code. You\u2019ll be testing it with the Test::More ecosystem, you\u2019ll be using `git` for change management.\rAnd the bad news is that you\u2019ll also be working on a web-app at this job.\rBut there\u2019s good news too! This web-app saves lives, and literally pushes forward medical science. Your work will be used by the NHS, research labs, and healthcare providers worldwide to diagnose patients, organize research, and make the world a better place.\rThat\u2019s a web-app that matters.", "Desired skills:": "You\u2019ve used DBIx::Class on a production project before \u2013 you know the difference in result between querying a resultset in an array vs a scalar context; bonus points if you\u2019ve a strong working knowledge of Postgres\r\n    Exposure to a Modern Perl framework, ideally one of Catalyst, Dancer or Mojolicious\r\n    Experience of the following would also be handy: git, Template Toolkit, Docker (and Kubernetes), Moose, Plack, Scrum", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "pete@perl.careers"}
{"Posted:": "August 26, 2020", "Company name:": "n/a", "Location:": "United States", "Country:": "United States", "Pay rate:": "Negotiable, DOE", "Poster represents:": "an independent contractor", "Terms of employment:": "Hourly employee", "Hours:": "Part time", "Onsite:": "no", "Description:": "Can work from home, and hours are negotiable, although I'll have some specific advanced perl questions that may require responses in less than 2 business days.  Rate will be hourly.  You should have a minimum of 5 years experience in perl, working specifically on perl projects for a minimum of 20 hours per week for 5 years straight, or 3 years experience working on perl full time.", "Desired skills:": "You should be fluent in spoken and written English.  Need assistance keeping modules updated, while maintaining a stable production environment.  Knowledge of perlbrew, or other perl revision systems is helpful.  You should be able to load modules manually with all dependencies isolated from all other environments, and test scripts without loading default modules.  You should also have experience with projects over 10,000 lines of code.", "Contact information:": "coriding@yahoo.com"}
{"Posted:": "December  9, 2020", "Company name:": "MSTS", "Location:": "Overland Park, KS or Remote", "Country:": "United States", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "At MSTS, we believe in continuous improvement through disruptive innovation. By harnessing 40 years of experience, technology investments and a desire to help businesses reach their full potential, we have expanded our portfolio of credit and payments technology solutions and blended them with a unique local touch that drives deeply into geo-specific business processes and payments.\rWe create value for our business partners by delivering innovative solutions and logistics through a global team of local professionals.  We are growing and adding new team members to our Engineering Department. We are looking for dynamic, results oriented, enthusiastic individuals who thrive in a fast paced environment and enjoy staying up to date on technologies.\rOur Application Stack:\rRuby and Ruby on Rails\r\nPerl\r\nJavaScript, Quasar, HTML, CSS\r\nOracle 19c\r\nDocker, Helm, Kubernetes\r\nGitlab\r\nAWS Technologies: SNS, SQS, S3, RDS (Oracle 19c), Lambda\rQualification:\r3+ years of web application development\r\nExperience building or working with complex applications\r\nFamiliarity with modern front-end build pipelines and tools\r\n1+ year Unix/Linux environment experience\rYour qualifications will stand out if you have:\rExperience with Ruby and Ruby on Rails\r\nExperience with Docker + Kubernetes\r\nExperience with multiple modern JavaScript frameworks\r\nOracle RDBMS and Oracle PL/SQL experience\r\nExperience working in an Agile environment\rIdeal Attributes:\rFocus on continuous learning and improvement\r\nDemonstrated initiative\r\nSelf-motivated and confident with an ownership mentality\r\nWorks well in a team\r\nKeep up to date with industry trends that would benefit our stack\rWhy you will love working at MSTS:\rCompetitive salary\r\nGenerous paid time off\r\nMedical, dental, vision, FSA, Life/AD&D, long and short term disability\r\n401K matching\r\nCasual environment and dress\r\nEmployee referral program\rAt MSTS we believe:\rin saying yes to unique and challenging requirements\r\nempowered team members are creative team members\r\nour products make the customer\u2019s day just a little bit better\r\nwork/life balance makes us all more effective\rMSTS is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer.  We welcome all veterans and disabled applicants.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Apply on the website"}
{"Posted:": "September 11, 2020", "Company name:": "Best Energy", "Location:": "Bristol, UK", "Pay rate:": "\u00a340k to \u00a350k", "Poster represents:": "an employer", "Terms of employment:": "Salaried employee", "Hours:": "Full time", "Onsite:": "some", "Description:": "We are looking to recruit a self-motivated and passionate, experienced Perl developer with a good understanding of Linux operating systems. General knowledge of operating hardware, interfacing to cloud systems and protocols such as MQTT, HTTP, Modbus, Bacnet and others, which will be required to fulfil the product developments.\r\nPrevious knowledge of energy monitoring, Cloud systems, web development, Python, PHP and IoT helpful but not essential.\r\nGood interpersonal skills that will fit in with this friendly and relaxed workplace.\r\nIdeal candidate located in the southwest, for access to Bristol area as and when required. Possibility of remote and flexible working.\r\nCareer development is supported and encouraged within the team.\rThe R&D office is currently located in St Austell but we are moving to Bristol very shortly.", "Desired skills:": "Maintain and update existing Perl software.\r\nDesign and implement new Python software for the future world order.\r\nFault-find and bug fix existing systems.\r\nImplement and improve automated testing systems.\r\nSupport the customer facing teams to resolve issue in the field.\r\nAid the building of a larger development team.\r\nContinuous improvement of working practices and procedures.\r\nWorking closely with Hardware and Cloud developers.", "Website for more information:": "", "Contact information:": "Please apply through our linkedin page"}
